FT  28 MAY 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pepper: the world demand and supply situation suggests that pepper prices in
general should be expected to increase. Rising coffee and cocoa prices might
tempt farmers and dealers in the Far East to concentrate on those
commodities rather than pepper which can be stored for a longer period. This
might result in a further tightness in supplies.
White pepper - a slightly steadier undertone for new crop positions. Spot
offered at USDollars 2,650, new crop: July/Oct shipment was traded at
Dollars 2,575 cif. Further forward offered at Dollars 2,600. Handpicked
quality further forward was unavailable. Black pepper - the on prices from
india and Lampong disappeared. Sarawak and Brazil were not competitive
sellers. The market is fully steady. India mg1 1675/1700.
