<HEADLINE>
FT  28 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Liffe seeks Pounds 10m via rights issue
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTONIA SHARPE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Liffe, London's financial futures and options exchange, hopes to raise up to
Pounds 10m through a rights issue which it says is primarily aimed at
addressing the demand for trading permits.
Liffe plans to issue 'quarter-shares' by way of a bonus which may be
converted into full A,B,C or E shares on a 4-for-1 basis. A share in Liffe
entitles the holder to a permit which allows them to trade specific
products.
Holders of A shares can trade in all futures, B shares in all financial
options, C shares in all futures except long gilt and short sterling
contracts, D shares in all equity options, and E shares in all futures
except long gilt, short sterling, bund and Euro-mark contracts.
Liffe said the issue would provide for a 25 per cent increase in each
relevant category of trading permit. The amounts payable on conversion are:
Pounds 50,000 for A shares, Pounds 25,000 for B and C shares and Pounds
6,250 for E shares.
Mr Nick Durlacher, Liffe's chairman, said the issue would overcome the
potential constraints on the further development of futures and financial
options business on Liffe.
</TEXT>
