FT  28 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Villiers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Villiers Group carried a provision of Pounds 1.52m in its first half
accounts related to its withdrawal from the oil industry.
The USM-traded group reported a pre-tax loss of Pounds 1.86m (Pounds 1.15m)
for the six months to January 31. Losses per share were 1.83p (2.25p).
