<HEADLINE>
FT  28 MAY 94 / UK Company News: BM
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BM Group said its debt reduction programme was on track as it announced the
disposal of a lossmaking machinery distribution business in the US, which is
expected to cut borrowings by Pounds 14m.
BM is selling Illinois-based Roland Machinery for Dollars 7.8m (Pounds
5.2m), plus repayment of a Dollars 1.9m intercompany loan. The sale will
also eliminate some Pounds 8m in stock finance previously taken into the
parent's Pounds 98m debt figure.
</TEXT>
