<HEADLINE>
FT  28 MAY 94 / UK Company News: BEP rises Pounds 1m to Pounds 5.1m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Turnover at Bristol Evening Post, the publisher, printer and distributor of
newspapers, dipped from Pounds 60.62m to Pounds 59.48m for the year ended
March 31 1994, but pre-tax profits improved by Pounds 1m to Pounds 5.1m.
Earnings per share were 12.98p, compared with 10.96p, while the dividend is
stepped up to 12.25p (11.75p) with a final payment of 8p.
The group also announced the purchase, through its Bristol United Press
subsidiary, of a Goss offset press from Rockwell Graphic Systems for Pounds
13m.
</TEXT>
