<HEADLINE>
FT  28 MAY 94 / World News in Brief: Tamils freed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Two Sri Lankan Tamils convicted in 1988 of a triple murder in a firebomb
attack on a house in east London were cleared and freed by the Court of
Appeal.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
