FT  27 MAY 94 / International Capital Markets: Representative office in
Beijing for Lehman Bros
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TONY WALKER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BEIJING
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Lehman Brothers, the US investment bank, has opened a representative office
in Beijing providing more evidence of the involvement of American financial
houses in China.
Mr Sherman Lewis, Lehman Brothers' vice-chairman, said the company would
involve itself in fund-raising for infrastructure projects, the marketing of
'various debt instruments' and assisting with public offerings for larger
enterprises.
Lehman acted as sole agent for the Construction Bank of China in a private
placement of debt securities in the US last August. It lead-managed last
October's Dollars 300m dragon bond and is assisting a large Chinese
corporation in a public offering.
The US investment house plans to open an office in Shanghai by the end of
the year.
