FT  27 MAY 94 / International Company News: AirTouch in Belgian move
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
AirTouch Communications, the US wireless communications group, is to spend
up to Dollars 147m to take a 25 per cent stake in Belgacom Mobile, a new
mobile communicatons company being formed by Belgacom, the Belgian
telecommunications company.
The joint venture company will include Belgacom's analog and digital
cellular businesses. Belgacom launched a new ditigal service, using the
European GSM standard, last January. It now serves over 30,000 customers and
covers over 80 per cent of Belgium.
AirTouch, previously knowns as PacTel - was selected by Belgacom to provide
support for the GSM launch. Mr Sam Ginn, chairman of AirTouch, said
yesterday's agreement in principle would allow the two to 'formalise our
relationship and continue to build on our achievements'.
</TEXT>
