</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Texaco, the US oil group, confirmed that it plans to sell an oilfield in
Colombia, as well as a pipeline that connects the field to a refinery owned
by the government, Reuter reports from New York.
A Texaco spokesman said the company would keep its downstream operations in
Colombia. 'We are not leaving the country,' he said.
