FT  27 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Atkins falls Pounds 252,000 into the red
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Atkins Group, the Leicestershire-based hosiery manufacturer, swung from
profits of Pounds 448,000 to losses of Pounds 252,000 pre-tax for the 12
months to April 2.
The directors warned in February that the year-end results would be
substantially lower because of a sharp slowdown in trading during the final
quarter.
