<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Warner Estate declines
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BLACKWELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Warner Estate Holdings, the property investment company, yesterday announced
pre-tax profits of Pounds 3.66m for the six months to end-March, down from a
previous Pounds 3.76m.
Turnover increased from Pounds 5.41m to Pounds 5.89m. The interim dividend
is 3.85p (3.65p) while earnings per share were 5.65p (5.43p).
Rental income increased from Pounds 4.25m to Pounds 4.48m. The directors
said the increase reflected the purchase of properties. They expected rental
income to continue to grow.
Turnover also included Pounds 890,000 (nil) from property trading and Pounds
515,000 (Pounds 1.16m) from specialised contracting.
